==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Topography
<hw>To*pog"ra*phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>topographie</ets>, Gr. <?/; <?/ a place + <?/ to write.]</ety>
<def>The description of a particular place, town, manor, parish, or
tract of land; especially, the exact and scientific delineation and
description in minute detail of any place or region.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Topography</xex>, as the description of particular
places, is distinguished from <xex>chorography</xex>, the description of
a region or a district, and for <xex>geography</xex>, the description of
the earth or of countries.</note> <rj><au>Brande & C.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Topologist</ent>⟦br⟧
